Incident Description:
After the transfer of SCP-015's mass to the site, a number of anomalous changes have begun to develop. Notably, SCP-015's growth rate has significantly increased compared to previously recorded rates, requiring several sessions of scheduled maintenace a day. This has placed an unforeseen burden on the site's staff, and so immediate action is required.

Recommended Action: 
Continuous observation and care are required until we can find an automated solution or some other alleviation.

Addendum 015-D-1, Urgent Action Notice:
After an additional week of observation post-transfer, significant structural damage has been identified within the containment chamber; the walls of the chamber frequently crumble as SCP-015 undergoes rapid expansion, which has required an increased amount of ongoing repair efforts to maintain. It is unclear if these behavioral changes are permanent or environmental in nature. Further testing is necessary to decide whether or not SCP-015 should be re-transferred to its original holding site.